http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Navy-chopper-makes-emergency-landing/article14024420.ece

A technical snag forced a naval Chetak helicopter to make emergency landing on a beach near Alappuzha, some 14 nautical miles south of the city on Wednesday.The helicopter (tail number IN-480) was on a routine sortie when it developed a technical glitch, resulting in the landing on the beach at 11.30 a.m.The aircraft or the crew did not suffer any damage, the Navy said.“A team from the Naval Base was despatched to assist the crew and after rectification of the fault, which was minor, the aircraft returned to Kochi,” said a naval spokesperson.